{"parentUuid":"e7b84548-6de8-4311-8177-ae3e3425351f","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"b877c76e-a199-4f7c-9efc-f567f0dbca98","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARiVXApo93nUDDH5tYi8Xn","type":"tool_result","content":"15\t\n16\t## Examples\n17\t\n18\tRun a replication that overwrites differing target refs, and fail instead of falling back to local materialization:\n19\t\n20\t```bash\n21\tgit-sync replicate \\\n22\t  --stats \\\n23\t  https://github.com/source-org/source-repo.git \\\n24\t  https://github.com/target-org/target-repo.git\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\tIf `replicate` cannot use relay against the target, it fails and tells you to rerun with `sync`.\n28\t\n29\tFor very large initial migrations, add `--target-max-pack-bytes` to split the initial pack into multiple smaller batches. The same flag works on `sync`, since `sync` auto-bootstraps on empty targets:\n30\t\n31\t```bash\n32\tgit-sync sync \\\n33\t  --target-max-pack-bytes 536870912 \\\n34\t  --protocol v2 \\\n35\t  -v \\\n36\t  <source-url> \\\n37\t  <target-url>\n38\t```\n39\t\n40\tAdd `--measure-memory` to any command to sample elapsed time and Go heap usage:\n41\t\n42\t```bash\n43\tgit-sync sync \\\n44\t  --measure-memory \\\n45\t  --json \\\n46\t  <source-url> \\\n47\t  <target-url>\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\t## Sync Behavior\n51\t\n52\t`sync` picks the bootstrap relay path automatically when the target is empty. For non-empty targets, safe fast-forward updates also use a relay path that streams the source pack directly into target `receive-pack` without local materialization. Anything not relay-eligible (force, prune, deletes, tag retargets) falls back to a materialized path bounded by `--materialized-max-objects`.\n53\t\n54\tSync specific branches:\n55\t\n56\t```bash\n57\tgit-sync sync \\\n58\t  --branch main,release \\\n59\t  --source-token \"$GITSYNC_SOURCE_TOKEN\" \\\n60\t  --target-token \"$GITSYNC_TARGET_TOKEN\" \\\n61\t  <source-url> \\\n62\t  <target-url>\n63\t```\n64\t\n65\tMap a source branch to a different target branch:\n66\t\n67\t```bash\n68\tgit-sync sync \\\n69\t  --map main:stable \\\n70\t  <source-url> \\\n71\t  <target-url>\n72\t```\n73\t\n74\tMirror tags and prune managed target refs that disappeared from source:\n75\t\n76\t```bash\n77\tgit-sync sync \\\n78\t  --tags \\\n79\t  --prune \\\n80\t  <source-url> \\\n81\t  <target-url>\n82\t```\n83\t\n84\tForce source-side protocol v2:\n85\t\n86\t```bash\n87\tgit-sync sync \\\n88\t  --protocol v2 \\\n89\t  <source-url> \\\n90\t  <target-url>\n91\t```\n92\t\n93\t## JSON Output\n94\t\n95\tAdd `--json` to any command to emit machine-readable output instead of the default text format.\n96\t\n97\tThe JSON interface is stable:\n98\t\n99\t- keys use `camelCase`\n100\t- refs and hashes are serialized as strings, not raw byte arrays\n101\t- top-level keys include `plans`, `pushed`, `skipped`, `blocked`, `deleted`, `dryRun`, `protocol`, and `stats`, plus `relay`, `relayMode`, `relayReason`, `batching`, `batchCount`, `plannedBatchCount`, and `tempRefs`\n102\t- each item in `plans` includes stable string fields such as `branch`, `sourceRef`, `targetRef`, `sourceHash`, `targetHash`, `kind`, `action`, and `reason`\n103\t\n104\t## Auth"}]},"uuid":"4caad5b5-724b-4d61-b82f-7b87106372f6","timestamp":"2026-05-04T10:30:09.540Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync/docs/usage.md","content":"\n## Examples\n\nRun a replication that overwrites differing target refs, and fail instead of falling back to local materialization:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync replicate \\\n  --stats \\\n  https://github.com/source-org/source-repo.git \\\n  https://github.com/target-org/target-repo.git\n```\n\nIf `replicate` cannot use relay against the target, it fails and tells you to rerun with `sync`.\n\nFor very large initial migrations, add `--target-max-pack-bytes` to split the initial pack into multiple smaller batches. The same flag works on `sync`, since `sync` auto-bootstraps on empty targets:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --target-max-pack-bytes 536870912 \\\n  --protocol v2 \\\n  -v \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\nAdd `--measure-memory` to any command to sample elapsed time and Go heap usage:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --measure-memory \\\n  --json \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\n## Sync Behavior\n\n`sync` picks the bootstrap relay path automatically when the target is empty. For non-empty targets, safe fast-forward updates also use a relay path that streams the source pack directly into target `receive-pack` without local materialization. Anything not relay-eligible (force, prune, deletes, tag retargets) falls back to a materialized path bounded by `--materialized-max-objects`.\n\nSync specific branches:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --branch main,release \\\n  --source-token \"$GITSYNC_SOURCE_TOKEN\" \\\n  --target-token \"$GITSYNC_TARGET_TOKEN\" \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\nMap a source branch to a different target branch:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --map main:stable \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\nMirror tags and prune managed target refs that disappeared from source:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --tags \\\n  --prune \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\nForce source-side protocol v2:\n\n```bash\ngit-sync sync \\\n  --protocol v2 \\\n  <source-url> \\\n  <target-url>\n```\n\n## JSON Output\n\nAdd `--json` to any command to emit machine-readable output instead of the default text format.\n\nThe JSON interface is stable:\n\n- keys use `camelCase`\n- refs and hashes are serialized as strings, not raw byte arrays\n- top-level keys include `plans`, `pushed`, `skipped`, `blocked`, `deleted`, `dryRun`, `protocol`, and `stats`, plus `relay`, `relayMode`, `relayReason`, `batching`, `batchCount`, `plannedBatchCount`, and `tempRefs`\n- each item in `plans` includes stable string fields such as `branch`, `sourceRef`, `targetRef`, `sourceHash`, `targetHash`, `kind`, `action`, and `reason`\n\n## Auth","numLines":90,"startLine":15,"totalLines":138}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e7b84548-6de8-4311-8177-ae3e3425351f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/git-sync","sessionId":"0cd46975-a945-4e8b-b0fa-f6cf392e38b2","version":"2.1.123","gitBranch":"main"}
